api_list.name: listPayoutMethodTypes
api_list.description: Retrieve a list of payout method types that you can use when creating a payout. The response contains a list of objects. Each object includes a payout method type and its attributes.

optional_parameters.name: is_cancelable
optional_parameters.description: Indicates whether the payout can be canceled. Relevant when category is cash.

optional_parameters.name: payout_currency
optional_parameters.description: Currency received by the beneficiary. Three-letter ISO 4217 code.

optional_parameters.name: starting_after
optional_parameters.description: The name of a payout method in the list. The list begins with the record that was created next after the record with this payout method. Use this filter to get the next page of results. Relevant when ending_before is not used.

optional_parameters.name: ending_before
optional_parameters.description: The name of a payout method in the list. The list ends with the last record that was created before the record with this payout method. Use this filter to get the previous page of results.

optional_parameters.name: is_location_specific
optional_parameters.description: Indicates whether the payout must be made at a specific physical location. Relevant when category is cash.

optional_parameters.name: beneficiary_country
optional_parameters.description: Country of the beneficiary. Two-letter ISO 3166-1 ALPHA-2 code.

optional_parameters.name: sender_entity_type
optional_parameters.description: Filters the type of entity for the payer. One of the following: individual, company

optional_parameters.name: beneficiary_entity_type
optional_parameters.description: Filters the type of entity for the beneficiary. One of the following: individual, company

optional_parameters.name: category
optional_parameters.description: The category of payout method. One of the following: bank, card, cash, rapyd_ewallet, ewallet

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: The maximum number of payout methods to return. Range: 1-100. Default is 10.

optional_parameters.name: sender_country
optional_parameters.description: Country of the sender. Two-letter ISO 3166-1 ALPHA-2 code. Note: This field does not appear in the response.

optional_parameters.name: sender_currency
optional_parameters.description: Currency that the sender is paying with. Three-letter ISO 4217 code.

optional_parameters.name: is_expirable
optional_parameters.description: Indicates whether the payout expires if not completed. Relevant when category is cash.

api_list.name: listPayouts
api_list.description: Retrieve a list of payouts that you created.

optional_parameters.name: beneficiary
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the beneficiary ID. String starting with beneficiary_.

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: The maximum number of payouts to return. Range: 1-100. Default is 10.

optional_parameters.name: sender_country
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the country of the sender. Two-letter ISO 3166-1 ALPHA-2 code.

optional_parameters.name: sender_currency
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the currency that the sender is paying with. Three-letter ISO 4217 code.

optional_parameters.name: ewallet
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the wallet ID. String starting with ewallet_.

optional_parameters.name: created_before
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the payout created after the last payout you want to retrieve. String starting with payout_.

optional_parameters.name: merchant_reference_id
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the merchant reference ID.

optional_parameters.name: ending_before
optional_parameters.description: The ID of a payout in the list. The list ends with the payout that was created before the payout with this ID. Use this filter to get the previous page of results. String starting with payout_. Deprecated.

optional_parameters.name: sender
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the sender ID. String starting with sender_.

optional_parameters.name: payout_method_type
optional_parameters.description: Filters according to the type of payout method. The two-letter prefix must match the beneficiary country code.

optional_parameters.name: created_after
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the payout created before the first payout you want to retrieve. String starting with payout_.

optional_parameters.name: starting_after
optional_parameters.description: The ID of a payout in the list. The list begins with the payout that was created next after the payout with this ID. Use this filter to get the next page of results. Relevant when ending_before is not used. String starting with payout_. Deprecated

api_list.name: getPayoutRequiredFields
api_list.description:
Retrieve the fields required to use a payout method type. The fields are returned as an array of objects. The name of each field appears in the name field of each object. Use this information for Create Payout, Create Beneficiary and Create Sender.
 Note: The fields returned by this method are required when you create a payout. If you create a payout with a sender or beneficiary that was created previously, you are responsible for choosing a sender and beneficiary that have all the fields required by the payout method.

required_parameters.name: pomt
required_parameters.description: (Required) The type of the payout method. Set to the name of a payout method listed in the response to List Payout Method Types. The two-letter prefix must match the beneficiary country code.

optional_parameters.name: beneficiary_entity_type
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Type of entity for the beneficiary. One of the following, individual, company

optional_parameters.name: sender_entity_type
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Type of entity for the sender. One of the following: individual, company

optional_parameters.name: payout_amount
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Amount of the payout, in units of the currency that the beneficiary is receiving. Decimal.

optional_parameters.name: sender_country
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Country of the sender. Two-letter ISO 3166-1 ALPHA-2 code. Uppercase.

optional_parameters.name: beneficiary_country
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Country of the beneficiary. Two-letter ISO 3166-1 ALPHA-2 code. Uppercase.

optional_parameters.name: payout_currency
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Currency received by the beneficiary. Three-letter ISO 4217 code. Uppercase.

optional_parameters.name: sender_currency
optional_parameters.description: (Required) Currency that the sender is paying with. Three-letter ISO 4217 code. Uppercase.
